the workplace, or government. But this is the first book about something much more fundamental: how the internet is transforming our collective intelligence and our understanding of the world. From the collaborative mathematicians of the Polymath Project to the amateur astronomers of Galaxy Zoo, Reinventing Discovery tells the exciting story of the unprecedented new era in networked science. It will interest anyone who wants to learn about how the online world is revolutionizing scientific discovery-and why the revolution is just beginning.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aDiscoveries in science. 0aInformation networks. 0aInformation technology. 0aInternet. 0aResearchxTechnological innovations. 7aSCIENCE / Research & Methodology.2bisacsh1 aNielsen, Michael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691202853zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691202853423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691202853.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles